    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": [
        "### Phase 3: Association Rule Mining (Apriori) for Crash Diagnostics\n",
        "To transition from anomaly detection to root-cause diagnostics, I isolated the hard-crash telemetry (`OOM_Exception` and `ANR_Timeout`). Using the Apriori algorithm for frequent pattern mining, I engineered a diagnostic matrix to mathematically isolate toxic infrastructure combinations. By evaluating Support, Confidence, and Lift metrics, the pipeline autonomously identifies the exact combinations of OS versions, RAM constraints, and specific SDKs responsible for fatal thread-blocking and memory leaks, eliminating manual DevOps debugging."
      ],
      "metadata": {
        "id": "pVS7aBK0nwOH"
      }
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": [
        "import pandas as pd\n",
        "from mlxtend.frequent_patterns import apriori, association_rules\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Isolating Hard Crashes for Root Cause Analysis...\")\n",
        "\n",
        "# 1. Filter only the hard crashes\n",
        "df_crashes = df[df['crash_type'] != 'None'].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "# 2. Prepare the diagnostic matrix\n",
        "# We only care about the environment that caused the crash\n",
        "diagnostic_features = df_crashes[['ram_mb', 'os_version', 'ad_network', 'ad_type', 'crash_type']].astype(str)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 3. One-Hot Encode (Apriori requires boolean matrices)\n",
        "basket = pd.get_dummies(diagnostic_features)\n",
        "# Convert all values to boolean (True/False)\n",
        "basket = basket.astype(bool)\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"Mining Toxic Combinations using Apriori...\")\n",
        "# 4. Generate frequent itemsets (combinations that appear in at least 5% of crashes)\n",
        "frequent_itemsets = apriori(basket, min_support=0.01, use_colnames=True)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 5. Generate Association Rules (Lower threshold to catch high-frequency crashes)\n",
        "rules = association_rules(frequent_itemsets, metric=\"confidence\", min_threshold=0.6)\n",
        "\n",
        "# 6. Filter for rules that lead to a specific crash type\n",
        "def get_crash_reasons(crash_name):\n",
        "    crash_rules = rules[rules['consequents'] == {f'crash_type_{crash_name}'}].copy()\n",
        "\n",
        "    # FORCE the AI to only show root causes that involve the Ad Network and Hardware\n",
        "    crash_rules['has_network'] = crash_rules['antecedents'].apply(lambda x: any('ad_network' in item for item in x))\n",
        "    crash_rules = crash_rules[crash_rules['has_network']]\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Sort by Lift to find the strongest toxic combinations\n",
        "    return crash_rules.sort_values(by='lift', ascending=False)[['antecedents', 'confidence', 'lift']].head(3)\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Root Cause: OOM_Exception (Memory Leaks) ---\")\n",
        "print(get_crash_reasons('OOM_Exception'))\n",
        "\n",
        "print(\"\\n--- Root Cause: ANR_Timeout (Freezes) ---\")\n",
        "print(get_crash_reasons('ANR_Timeout'))"
      ],
